"use client";

/* =============================================================================
   AlgeriaGlobe — true 3D globe rendition
   -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
   A Cloudflare "Region: Earth"–style globe centered on Algeria.

   - Real orthographic sphere projection: every dot is a (lng, lat) point
     projected through the sphere with the camera looking at North Africa.
   - World coastlines (1:110m, public domain Natural Earth) at coarse density.
   - Algeria sampled at 3× the density so it visually stands out — bright
     against the dimmer rest-of-world dots.
   - Camera positioned to put Algeria dead-center on the front face, like
     the US sits centered in Cloudflare's globe.
   - Continuous slow rotation around the polar axis, with a slight forward
     tilt that doesn't change.
   - Dots fade out near the limb (sphere edge) so the globe feels rounded.
   - Latitude/longitude grid lines drawn as great-circle arcs.
   - 8 city pins for our launch cities. Pins on the back hemisphere are culled.
   - Travel arcs curve through 3D space between cities, fade in/out.
   - Click → all visible pins flash + arc cascade. Spin doesn't accelerate
     (the dots already rotate; a click adds the visual punch).

   Pure SVG. No Three.js. Coastline data baked at build time, ~25KB embedded.
   ============================================================================= */

